    "Candour runs in parallel, not sequence: the same incident may require the safeguarding referral, the CQC notification (gov-005 — candour incidents almost always notify), RIDDOR, and the SEA review (pc-001) — the candour clock does not pause for any of them, and the account given is 'what we know so far', updated as enquiries conclude",
    "The written follow-up completes the duty: sent promptly after the conversation, covering the same ground in plain language, and supplemented when the investigation concludes — the person hears the outcome from the service before they could hear it from anyone else",
