    "The doorstep sequence is fixed: (1) KNOCK AND WAIT properly — the person's own answer rhythm from dc-001 (slow walkers need minutes, not seconds), front and back doors where safe access exists, doorbell and knocker both; (2) LOOK AND LISTEN — milk and post accumulating, curtains against the time of day, lights against the hour, windows, the TV or radio sounding, movement, calls for help, the dog barking unusually; (3) PHONE — the person's numbers, twice, with voicemail left; (4) CHECK THE OBVIOUS — the keysafe presence (dc-002), the neighbour's knowledge where the person has agreed that contact, the visible signs of departure (car gone where relevant); (5) CALL THE OFFICE — everything found reported, the ladder decision made together; never leave before this call",
    "The office ladder then runs per dc-003: known contacts phoned (family, the agreed neighbour), telecare provider checked (pendant activity, last movement data where bb-001 systems exist), other services cross-checked (the day centre, the district nurse who visited earlier), and the attendance decision — return visit, family attends, or police welfare check — made against the person's criticality rating and the day's picture",
