    "Flexibility has honest boundaries — safe staffing, medication windows, other people's care — and the boundaries are told to the person plainly, because unexplained inflexibility reads as indifference.",
    "Today's 'no' is respected as fully as yesterday's 'yes': declining a shower, a meal or an outing changes today's care, not the person's reputation.",
